2. The words of an English sentence stand in a fixed order which shows their grammatical relation to each other. In Latin this relation is shown by inflection, and the order of the words represents their relative emphasis and importance in the writer’s or speaker’s mind.

3. The most emphatic place is the first,· next in importance is the last,· the weakest point is the middle.

4. As the most important word in the sentence is the subject, and the second in importance is the verb, these normally stand first and last respectively. Their respective modifiers stand next these
